      "question_pmp": "A project manager is new to a long-running software project that has been facing recurring budget overruns and schedule delays. To get a comprehensive understanding of the project's history and current status, the project manager reviews the project charter, previous lessons learned registers, change logs, and risk registers. The project manager notices a recurring pattern of unauthorized changes and a lack of clear documentation for budget approvals. What technique is the project manager using to identify these patterns?",
